<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1898-05-26T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1898-05-26T00:00:00-05:00" n="37" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d37">
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Day</persName> to Mr.
                                    <persName type="to">Tower</persName>.</hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>,<lb/><hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1898-05-26"><hi rend="italic">May 26,
                                1898</hi></date>.</dateline>
                            <seg rendition="#left">No. 111.]</seg></opener>
                        <p><hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: I have to inform you that your dispatch
                            No. 60, of the 29th ultimo, reporting that Mr. Ignatz Gutman voluntarily
                            enlisted in the Hungarian army, and thereby waived his rights as a
                            naturalized American citizen, is received.</p>
                        <p>Your course in regard to the matter is approved by the Department.</p>
                        <p>Respectfully, yours,</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">William R. Day.</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>